24:55.650 --> 24:57.993
There's something that I don't have.

25:00.277 --> 25:04.764
He died, he's raised, he's at the right hand of God.

25:05.866 --> 25:08.230
Whatever that looks like feels like is.

25:08.290 --> 25:13.618
The head that once was crowned with thorns is crowned with glory now.

25:13.922 --> 25:15.544
Jesus is the ascended king.

25:15.584 --> 25:18.747
He's in the place of dominion, the place of authority.

25:20.008 --> 25:22.610
He's exalted as the God-man.

25:22.650 --> 25:30.998
His human nature, his human nature, his physicality is now located somewhere.

25:34.902 --> 25:36.283
Yeah.

25:36.303 --> 25:43.410
And if his physical raised body is somewhere, and I know you're going to think that I'm

25:43.618 --> 25:50.047
a horrible person when I say what I'm about to say, and I am a horrible person, but I don't mean this in any horrible way.

25:50.949 --> 26:01.284
Since the risen Christ is physically present in heaven, he is not physically present in the Roman Catholic mass.

26:03.887 --> 26:04.168
Okay?

26:05.289 --> 26:11.218
So either we have him as an ascended king who is triumphed and his work is finished,

26:11.426 --> 26:14.249
so that we do not need another sacrifice.

26:14.269 --> 26:16.030
There is no other sacrifice.

26:16.071 --> 26:17.412
There is no other plea.

26:17.812 --> 26:22.317
It is enough that Jesus died and that he died for me once and for all.

26:22.677 --> 26:24.999
He was raised for our justification.

26:25.019 --> 26:28.903
He is ascended and is in the position of dominion and authority.

26:29.143 --> 26:40.114
No matter what the world says today, no matter Fox News, MSNBC, BBC, whatever else, the fact is Christ is the ascended king and nothing is out of control.

26:40.450 --> 26:47.237
And nothing is going to be out of control as long as he reigns in heaven until he returns.

26:48.339 --> 26:51.062
Since he is there, he is interceding.

26:56.928 --> 26:59.791
He's interceding for us, right?

27:00.392 --> 27:03.175
He said, well, I thought the Holy Spirit was interceding for us.

27:03.195 --> 27:09.522
Well, remember, they are distinct and they are united in the work of redemption.

27:09.794 --> 27:19.925
What is happening in the work of the Spirit, wherever we are, is happening in an amazing way in the presence of the Father before the throne of God above.

27:20.005 --> 27:22.568
I have a strong and perfect plea.

27:23.669 --> 27:34.041
On the basis of His ones for all work of atonement, He continues to secure for those who are His people all the benefits of His death.

27:35.703 --> 27:38.706
And so He asks another question in verse 35.

27:39.362 --> 27:43.048
Well, who then shall separate us from the love of Christ?

27:44.550 --> 27:53.966
And then he was honored, you will see in the text, to list potential enemies of our happiness and enemies of our security in Jesus.

27:55.528 --> 28:00.015
And once again, he returns to this matter of suffering.

28:01.277 --> 28:03.561
Who shall separate us from the love of Christ?

28:03.942 --> 28:06.706
Shout tribulation, suffering.

28:07.906 --> 28:14.656
You know, without a theology of suffering, we have very little to say to our friends and neighbors who suffer.

28:16.579 --> 28:30.900
It's surely one of the reasons that people who are really struggling with life find a devil to come into many of our congregations is because it just seems to be a sort of overwhelming sense of, hey, we've got it all together.

28:31.802 --> 28:34.386
You know, we've got it fixed.

28:34.406 --> 28:37.330
So the person says, well, it seems to me that all of it fixed.

28:37.538 --> 28:40.001
So I dare let them know how unfixed I am.

28:40.041 --> 28:52.374
Now that doesn't mean that we should pretend to be something we're not, but it does argue for us being honest enough with one another to say that we do know tribulation, that we do know suffering.

28:53.135 --> 29:06.450
And when we fail to do that, then we actually make it possible for us to be regarded as just quite silly with a kind of grin on your face.

29:06.946 --> 29:11.451
that even the worst visit to the orthodontist can't remove.

29:14.434 --> 29:18.519
Tears are part and parcel of God's provision for us.

29:20.481 --> 29:30.893
So Paul does what he does, and that is he quotes the Bible, who shall separate us from the love of Christ, tribulation, distress, persecution, famine, nakedness, danger, or the sword.

29:31.193 --> 29:32.214
And he says, no, you've got it.

29:32.234 --> 29:33.175
They're in Psalm 44.

29:34.597 --> 29:35.858
You've got it in the Bible.

29:36.610 --> 29:38.833
For your sake, we're being killed all the day long.

29:38.853 --> 29:41.958
We're regarded as sheep to be slaughtered.

29:43.100 --> 29:59.365
You know, we said yesterday, I did, that Romans 828 has the kind of potential for what we might call a shaving mirror verse, you know, or a little plaque at the end of your hallway.

29:59.946 --> 30:01.228
And we know that in all things.

30:01.328 --> 30:05.074
And if you don't have that one, then you might have

30:05.570 --> 30:07.993
Lamentations 3, 23, right?

30:08.794 --> 30:13.801
It's the greatest thy faithfulness, mercies are new every morning, greatest thy faithfulness.

30:14.702 --> 30:29.522
You know, there's not one person in a thousand that has actually read Lamentations chapter 3 and considered how it is that verse 23 is such a standout verse.

30:29.634 --> 30:39.305
Because all the surrounding contexts of lamentations, three, is all about giving your teeth ground and eating by tigers and everything else.

30:39.325 --> 30:40.886
And this is an expression of life.

30:41.727 --> 30:47.414
And so Jeremiah says, and it's this, and it's this, and it's this, and it's this, and it's this.

30:48.695 --> 30:55.823
Yet, he says, yet this I call to mind, right?

30:56.444 --> 30:58.546
You identity, you mentality.

30:58.978 --> 31:15.797
I don't say this is not true, this is not happening, this is true, this is happening, but this I call to mind, and therefore I have hope for your mercies are new every morning.

31:17.018 --> 31:18.400
Great is your faithfulness.

31:19.942 --> 31:25.208
You notice that it is in all these things that we're more than conquerors.

31:26.209 --> 31:27.410
We're not, this is not

31:27.522 --> 31:34.130
This is not flying a Gulf Stream at 53,000 feet above all the normal air traffic.

31:34.731 --> 31:37.455
This is actually flying in the clouds.

31:37.875 --> 31:39.798
This is flying in the turbulence.

31:39.818 --> 31:44.484
It is in all these things that we are more than conquerors.

31:45.485 --> 31:48.749
And that's why his rhetorical questions are over.

31:48.809 --> 31:55.538
And he moves to his great crescendo to move, if you like, from the law court.

31:55.842 --> 32:00.607
to the Cleveland Symphony Orchestra, and he makes two great declarations.

32:01.388 --> 32:04.491
Nothing separates us from God's love for us.

32:06.293 --> 32:08.816
For one, we are more than conquerors.

32:08.856 --> 32:12.320
The word that is used there in Greek is one of those compounded words.

32:13.041 --> 32:25.234
It's only that compounded nature of it can do justice to the victory that he's describing, which comes in the face of overwhelming odds, more than conquerors.

32:27.330 --> 32:31.916
in these things, in these things.

32:32.717 --> 32:37.202
I haven't quoted Andre Crouch yet, so I'm just going to throw him out now if that's okay.

32:39.585 --> 32:50.418
He came to Scotland in the early 70s and we had the privilege of going to a cinema somewhere in the town and it was just

32:50.562 --> 32:57.392
It was quite amazing that he could have such an impact on all these funny little Scottish people, myself included.

32:58.173 --> 33:03.500
And some of you who were at Expo 72 will remember he was there as well.

33:04.341 --> 33:11.511
And remember how he was able to sing.

33:11.632 --> 33:13.494
I've had many tears and sorrows.

33:14.275 --> 33:16.178
I have had questions for tomorrow.

33:18.274 --> 33:31.817
There have been times when I don't know right from wrong, but in every situation God gave me blessed consolation that my trials came to only make me stronger.

33:31.837 --> 33:34.181
Through it all, through it all.

33:35.182 --> 33:39.730
I learned to trust in Jesus, I learned to trust in God, through it all.

33:40.354 --> 33:42.316
I've learned to depend upon his word.

33:42.336 --> 33:49.064
So I thank him for the mountains, and I thank him for the valleys, and I thank him for the things he brought me through.

33:49.084 --> 33:54.049
Because if I'd never had a problem, I'd never know that God could solve them.

33:54.430 --> 33:58.254
I'd never know what faith in him could do through it all.

33:59.155 --> 34:05.422
That's what he's saying here, in all these things, through him who loved us.

34:06.223 --> 34:08.045
I am, therefore, convinced.

34:08.465 --> 34:09.266
I'm convinced.

34:09.410 --> 34:10.251
I'm persuaded.

34:10.271 --> 34:15.257
I am absolutely rock solid on this.

34:16.098 --> 34:20.083
What an encouragement it must have been to the initial readers, even as it is to us today.

34:20.904 --> 34:23.668
They were facing tribulation, danger, sword.

34:24.028 --> 34:25.890
Those things were all present realities.

34:26.932 --> 34:33.139
And any uncertainty coming from the pen of Paul would have had an impact on them that was negative.

34:33.159 --> 34:34.942
Well, he's not making it up.

34:35.582 --> 34:37.264
He's just telling the truth.

34:37.785 --> 34:38.546
I'm sure.

34:38.914 --> 34:41.197
and convinced and persuaded.

34:41.237 --> 34:43.520
It's actually the perfect tense.

34:44.421 --> 34:48.466
I have become and I remain convinced.

34:49.767 --> 34:52.491
I have become and I remain convinced.

34:52.911 --> 34:57.597
Persuaded, I think, is a good translation, for I'm sure, for I'm persuaded.

34:58.398 --> 35:02.924
In view of the process that he is outlining here, he's thought it out.

35:04.666 --> 35:08.210
Some of us just need to get to grips with it, so we've got to think it out.

35:08.642 --> 35:13.909
And as a result of thinking biblically, he is persuaded by what he knows.

35:14.930 --> 35:17.233
He is, if you like, since I mentioned flying.

35:17.654 --> 35:19.016
He's flying the instruments.

35:20.197 --> 35:21.419
He's flying the instruments.

35:22.140 --> 35:30.531
The other day when we went somewhere, goodness gracious, if they didn't have instruments in that plane, I don't know how we would have ever got on the ground.

35:31.232 --> 35:35.858
But the pilots not looking out of the window, I mean, you don't, we want them, don't want them to be.

35:36.194 --> 35:40.318
Now when you've got this, you know, an instrument landing system is doing its best.

35:40.718 --> 35:44.302
You don't want to be sitting up front for a number of reasons, but you don't want to be up there.

35:44.322 --> 35:49.507
And all of a sudden you hear, whoa, whoa, whoa, hey, hey, wait.

35:50.047 --> 35:52.229
You're like, no, where did that come from?

35:52.269 --> 35:53.450
That wasn't up there, was it?

35:53.751 --> 35:56.794
It says, whoa, fly the instruments.

35:57.334 --> 35:59.316
You don't feel it, fly the instruments.

36:01.298 --> 36:05.522
That's what, this is what I know of the

36:05.666 --> 36:14.878
my Lord and God, that fills my lips with praise, my heart with song.

36:16.119 --> 36:19.504
Not just what I feel of thee, my Lord and God.

36:20.064 --> 36:21.106
It is what I know.

36:21.146 --> 36:23.429
It's what I know.

36:23.749 --> 36:24.850
This is what he's saying.

36:25.872 --> 36:30.958
I'm sure that nothing can and nothing will separate us from God's love.

36:31.859 --> 36:34.002
And so he runs through a list of potential

36:34.210 --> 36:35.932
and actual adversaries.

36:37.334 --> 37:02.930
You don't need me to work my way through them all, but we just make a comment as we draw this to a close, death or life, separated by life, life with all its battles, life with all kinds of benefits, life with its trials, life with its temptations, death which like never rolling stream bears, all its sons away,

37:04.706 --> 37:34.098
As an atom all die, so in Christ shall all be made alive, comprehensive, either one or the other, nor angels or rulers or demons, the heavenly realms of spiritual benefit or spiritual wickedness, the unseen armies of darkness that have been disarmed at the cross of Christ, still playing out their game

37:34.338 --> 37:36.962
But checkmate is without question.

37:38.644 --> 37:39.245
Defeat it.

37:40.366 --> 37:41.628
The present or the future?

37:42.990 --> 37:43.951
What are you worried about?

37:43.971 --> 37:45.794
Well, I'm worried about the present.

37:45.994 --> 37:48.017
Oh, well, I'm worried about the future.

37:48.077 --> 37:48.658
Well, good.

37:48.698 --> 37:52.764
Well, let's get together and make a group for the present of the future.

37:52.824 --> 37:53.605
Fearfuls.

37:55.888 --> 37:56.729
Time comes in.

37:56.749 --> 38:00.274
I've only had a few really genius thoughts in my life.

38:00.994 --> 38:08.383
If I haven't had any genius thoughts in my life, I mean, I've had basic thoughts like junk is junk.

38:08.583 --> 38:09.284
That's a good one.

38:11.727 --> 38:16.753
But also, I figured out that the future comes in at the rate of 60 seconds a minute.

38:18.756 --> 38:20.157
I mean, all you need for that is a watch.

38:22.080 --> 38:26.125
So, you know, how are you doing?

38:27.206 --> 38:27.727
Pretty good.

38:29.269 --> 38:30.450
You make it for another minute?

38:31.394 --> 38:32.556
Yeah, I hope so, yeah.

38:33.177 --> 38:34.119
I'm trusting so.

38:34.159 --> 38:45.139
When you're waiting for your birthday and you're four years old or five years old, you're waiting for 20% of your life to pass.

38:48.085 --> 38:53.234
When you're 50 waiting for your birthday, you're waiting for 2% of your life to pass.

38:53.922 --> 38:57.267
The future is still coming in at the rate of 60 seconds a minute.

38:57.287 --> 39:04.637
But somehow or another, inside of us, it feels like it's just like it was only Christmas yesterday and apparently it's Christmas again tomorrow.

39:05.518 --> 39:06.900
It's a strange sensation.

39:07.821 --> 39:08.762
It chases us.

39:09.703 --> 39:11.286
The passage of time chases us.

39:11.646 --> 39:13.729
The passage of time changes us.

39:15.311 --> 39:17.294
One of the benefits of age is wisdom.

39:18.495 --> 39:22.000
One of the problems of age or the hazards of age is worry.

39:22.921 --> 39:23.442
Worry.

39:24.002 --> 39:25.604
I mean, you can't be a grandfather, too.

39:25.624 --> 39:26.686
You become a grandfather.

39:27.547 --> 39:32.234
And you suddenly realize when you become a grandfather, this is what my grandfather was on about.

39:32.996 --> 39:49.961
When, in the 1960s in Glasgow, he sees the emergence of the Beatles and the Rolling Stones and the who and the trucks and the tremolo's and all the wrong rest of them.

39:49.981 --> 39:53.106
And he used to say to me, son, son,

39:53.634 --> 39:56.978
And he was a veteran of the First World War, the Battle of the Song.

39:57.578 --> 40:10.473
He said, son, if people had walked down the main street, if Glasgow, when I was a boy and looked like that, they would have put them in a very special place.

40:11.534 --> 40:15.359
And then he would say, I don't know what's going to become of you.

40:16.260 --> 40:17.081
I really don't.

40:17.922 --> 40:21.746
Now I find myself doing the jolly same thing, not about the Beatles.

40:21.954 --> 40:40.917
But if you do the math with your grandchildren, am I the only one that lies in his bed and goes, OK, if I'm 73 now and there's a new baby about to come in February, that means that by the time that person is 10 years old, if they live, I will be 83 years old.

40:41.338 --> 40:45.563
And the one who is presently 15, goodness only knows how all of them are going to be there.

40:45.583 --> 40:48.306
And you can drive yourself completely crazy.

40:50.274 --> 40:52.636
But you never be separated from the love of Christ.

40:52.656 --> 40:54.598
You might be separated from sanity.

40:57.541 --> 41:02.125
If you find yourself doing the whole thing, have you ever seen anything like this in your life?

41:03.066 --> 41:05.228
I don't know what it's going to be like for our grandchildren.

41:05.549 --> 41:06.890
Hey, welcome to the world.

41:08.171 --> 41:09.632
It's actually very arrogant.

41:10.793 --> 41:17.400
As if somehow or another, we think that God is taking his hand off the controls of the universe as soon as we get out of here.

41:18.541 --> 41:19.762
He got us covered.

41:19.874 --> 41:24.401
But we're not, we don't believe he's got our kids covered, or our grandchildren covered.

41:24.421 --> 41:26.124
What happens when John MacArthur dies?

41:26.404 --> 41:27.907
What happens when this guy dies?

41:27.967 --> 41:29.269
What happens when this guy dies?

41:29.790 --> 41:41.227
JC Ryle, the Bishop of Liverpool, had the answer to that when he said, don't worry about it for a moment, because God has yet brighter stars in his universe, and we may trust him.

41:41.748 --> 41:46.616
Neither present or future, neither height nor depth, or you get a little carried away on that.

41:46.636 --> 41:48.018
Neither height nor depth.

41:49.250 --> 42:01.286
If I make my bed in the heavens, if I go to the depths, Psalm 139, God is sovereign over time and over space.

42:02.127 --> 42:11.580
That's why the children, they do that song, not only, my God is so big, so strong and so mighty, but Jesus' love is very wonderful.

42:12.041 --> 42:13.002
That's what they say.

42:13.422 --> 42:15.485
Jesus' love is very wonderful.

42:16.306 --> 42:19.090
So high, you can't get over it.

42:19.554 --> 42:22.237
So low, you can't get under it.

42:23.299 --> 42:35.975
So we've got to teach that to our grandchildren, because the day will come when the temptation will be to believe that time and space may separate them from the love of God.

42:36.916 --> 42:43.664
Powers, nor powers, the forces of the universe, may the force go with you.

42:44.665 --> 42:44.986
Yeah.

42:46.047 --> 42:46.468
Yeah.

42:47.429 --> 42:48.370
The forces.

42:49.154 --> 42:50.396
forces of darkness.

42:50.436 --> 42:52.518
We wrestle not against flesh and blood.

42:53.079 --> 42:55.722
The gun and spiritual wickedness in the heavenly places.

42:56.764 --> 43:05.414
This today morning, my son sent me a picture taken on a notice board as he was walking to church in Manhattan.

43:06.356 --> 43:13.184
And it was a picture of a person that was an ill-defined picture you couldn't really tell the gender.

43:14.205 --> 43:17.970
And it said, we save ourselves.

43:19.554 --> 43:28.067
And down in small print, it said, embrace the freedom to choose whatever sex you want.

43:29.049 --> 43:32.634
Love once that comes from the deepest darkness.

43:33.696 --> 43:37.361
But those powers are held captive.

43:37.902 --> 43:45.714
In fact, if you think about it, where it not for the restraining grace of God, we would be living in hell.

43:46.690 --> 43:52.198
But God's sovereign restraining hand remains over all things.

43:53.520 --> 44:06.117
And so he says, it's kind of like, if he had somebody writing this for him, if he had a secretary, he said, nor angels, nor rulers, nor things present, or things to come, nor powers, nor height, nor dead.

44:06.578 --> 44:08.681
And then he said, anything else I should put in?

44:09.222 --> 44:12.426
And this secretary said, why just put nor anything else?

44:13.227 --> 44:14.329
And he said, well, that's good.

44:14.349 --> 44:15.250
Let's put that in.

44:15.586 --> 44:17.808
I'm just making that up, you understand.

44:18.189 --> 44:21.192
I'm not interfering with the inspiration of Scripture.

44:21.232 --> 44:29.600
I'm just saying that if there was an interactive element in it, if he wrote it all himself or whatever, nor anything else in all creation, no loopholes.

44:30.882 --> 44:31.502
No loopholes.

44:31.782 --> 44:32.663
It's comprehensive.

44:33.464 --> 44:39.590
Nothing can or will separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus, our Lord.

44:40.671 --> 44:43.154
And since we are in Christ,

44:43.714 --> 44:45.937
that is therefore now no condemnation.

44:47.679 --> 44:50.302
And there is actually no separation.

44:57.631 --> 45:00.594
Well, that's enough for now.

45:00.634 --> 45:01.255
Let me pray.

45:01.295 --> 45:06.562
Our Father, thank you that we have the Bible.

45:06.582 --> 45:13.490
Thank you that your word shines into the crevices and

45:15.234 --> 45:19.818
tiny parts of our lives when we're alone, when we're in the company of others.

45:21.160 --> 45:26.865
It convinces, it convinces us, it turns us unreservedly to Jesus.

45:27.826 --> 45:38.756
We recognize that the work of the evil one is to unsettle, to undo, to rob us of a sense of convinced assurance.

45:39.637 --> 45:44.562
But we thank you that our birthright in Jesus is

45:44.866 --> 45:47.971
to assure us of the things that we've been considering.

45:48.753 --> 46:11.090
And so we pray that it may be in that renewed sense of an understanding of the immensity of your love towards us, and of your care for us, such as we've just been pondering, that that may set our gaze in the right direction, that it might place our feet in the pathway of your appointing.

46:11.650 --> 46:16.235
and that it might set our hands free to love and serve others.

46:17.376 --> 46:19.038
And we ask this in Christ's name.

46:20.039 --> 46:20.420
Amen.

